# Hive Strategy — PR Review System

This project has an autonomous three-agent PR review pipeline that runs on every pull request:

1. **Reviewer agent** (`skills/pr-review/reviewer.py`) — reads the diff, posts inline comments for bugs/security/perf issues
2. **Programmer agent** (`skills/pr-review/debater.py`) — argues back or accepts each comment, posts reply threads
3. **Fixer agent** (`skills/pr-review/fixer.py`) — auto-fixes accepted issues, commits and pushes back to the PR branch
4. **CI loop** (`.github/workflows/pr-review.yml`) — reruns on every push until no fixable issues remain (max 5 iterations)

All review threads are visible inline in Cursor via the GitHub Pull Requests extension.

## When the user asks about the current PR

Run these commands to gather context before answering:

```bash
# Get current PR number and title
gh pr view --json number,title,body,headRefName,baseRefName

# List open review comments (what the reviewer flagged)
gh pr view --json reviews --jq '.reviews[].body'

# Show inline comments with file + line context
gh api repos/ykita0224-work/hive-strategy/pulls/$(gh pr view --json number --jq .number)/comments \
  --jq '.[] | "[\(.path):\(.line)] \(.body[:120])"'

# Show debate replies (programmer agent responses)
gh api repos/ykita0224-work/hive-strategy/pulls/$(gh pr view --json number --jq .number)/comments \
  --jq '.[] | select(.in_reply_to_id != null) | "REPLY to \(.in_reply_to_id): \(.body[:120])"'
```

## When the user asks about a specific file or line

Always fetch the actual current content of the file before answering — do not rely solely on the diff.

## Key file locations

- `skills/pr-review/main.py` — entry point, orchestrates the full loop
- `skills/pr-review/reviewer.py` — Claude reviewer agent
- `skills/pr-review/debater.py` — Claude programmer/debate agent
- `skills/pr-review/fixer.py` — Claude auto-fix agent
- `skills/pr-review/github.py` — GitHub API client
- `.github/workflows/pr-review.yml` — CI workflow
- `.claude/commands/review.md` — `/review` slash command for running locally

## Running the review locally

```bash
# Load env and run against current branch's PR
set -a && source .env.local && set +a
PR_NUMBER=$(gh pr view --json number --jq .number)
REPO=ykita0224-work/hive-strategy PR_NUMBER=$PR_NUMBER python skills/pr-review/main.py
```
